verse.lines:
{lang-eng}Under the shadow of Thy throne
Thy saints have dwelt secure;
Sufficient is Thine arm alone,
And our defence is sure{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}A thousand ages in Thy sight
Are like an evening gone;
Short as the watch that ends the night
Before the rising sun.{/lang-eng}

{lang-eng}Time, like an ever-rolling stream,
Bears all its sons away;
They fly forgotten, as a dream
Dies at the opening day.{/lang-eng}
